  "text": "Of course, there is a principal restriction connected with the fact that a resonator has a narrow resonant line of transmission. This means that a resonator can be used as a limiter only at this particular wavelength while all radiation in the vicinity of this wavelength is reflected. However, there does exist a class of active laser systems as optical detection and ranging systems to which such a limiter can be applicable. It is also noteworthy that in the earliest proposal of an optical power limiter in 1962 a nonlinear Fabry-Perot resonator was considered as an ideal reflective limiter [CITATION_1] .",
